text: Survivor Series (2015) was a professional wrestling pay-per-view and livestreaming show made by WWE. It took place on November 22, 2015, at the Philips Arena in Atlanta, Georgia. It was the 28th Survivor Series event held by WWE. The event celebrated The Undertaker's 25th anniversary in WWE. Nine matches were performed at the event. In the scheduled main event, Roman Reigns became a world champion for the first time, when he defeated Dean Ambrose in a tournament final to win the vacant WWE World Heavyweight Championship. However, Sheamus cashed in his Money in the Bank contract and defeated Reigns to win the title for a third time (and his fourth world championship overall in WWE).
